lines.text: Read my lips--they're sealed.
This is Sydney Rutledge. Obviously, I'm not answering. So, leave me and message so I'll know whether I want to call you back or not.
It's amazing how you can juggle putting a pool party together, and a fall wardrobe in the same day.
What is this, a lame and moronic attempt at revenge?
I know someone who could get a girl to do just about anything, Countess.
Nancy, shut up and leave!
Ooh, I love myself!
Poor Mila is probably suffering from trauma too, dear.
She's suffering from drama, not trauma. Just a bad case of overacting.
If you ask me the whole thing is an oxymoron.
Excuse me?
It's just that in my book, slumber and party just don't seem to go together. Well, darling, my cook needs some suggestions as to what you angels like to eat.
Well, that's easy enough. For a good slumber party, one needs to usual finger foods- pretzels, potato chips, soda, natural and artificial.
Hold on, darling, I'm not a stenographer!
Ahh, Sydney. How to turn a backstabbing little duckling into a swan!
Does it look like I have Owen's calendar?
There goes superclusters!
Sydney, you never wear anything more than twice.
That's once too often.
Use your pedal!
